  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "Twenty-one short stories spanning the breadth of the Horus Heresy. Aaron Dembski-Bowden's Howl of the Hearthworld returns to Bjorn and the Space Wolves' Tra pack, while Lord of the Red Sands drops back into Angron's red-misted skull. Graham McNeill's Wolf Mother brings the Sisters of Silence into focus against psychic horror; James Swallow's All That Remains and Gunsight follow Nathaniel Garro on Knight-Errant missions for Malcador. Nick Kyme's The Phoenician and Chirurgeon turn to Fulgrim's transformation; Chris Wraight's Allegiance and Daemonology to White Scars caught between sides. Guy Haley, John French, David Annandale, Gav Thorpe and Rob Sanders fill out a mosaic that runs from Calth wreckage and Sigillite intrigue to traitor-legion oaths sworn in the dark.",
